a:18:{s:4:"name";s:7:"Alavert";s:11:"small_descr";s:186:"Alavert  is used to treat the symptoms of allergies, such as sneezing, watery eyes, and runny nose. It is also used to treat skin hives and itching in people with chronic skin reactions.";s:14:"small_descr_de";s:233:"Alavert ist für die Linderung der Symptome der saisonalen allergischen Erkrankungen wie Schnupfen, Niesen, juckende und  tränende Augen oder Juckreiz der Nase und der Haut bei den Patienten mit chronischen Hautreaktionen verwendet.";s:14:"small_descr_fr";s:250:"Alavert est utilisé pour traiter les symptômes d'allergies, tels que les éternuements, le larmoiement, le  coryza. Il est également utilisé pour traiter l'urticaire cutanées et la démangeaison aux personnes avec des réactions peau chroniques.";s:14:"small_descr_es";s:252:"Alavert es utilizado para el tratamiento de los síntomas de las alergias, como estornudo, ojos llorosos y resfriado. Es utilizado también para el tratamiento de la urticaria y la picazón de la piel de las personas con reacciones cutáneas crónicas.";s:14:"small_descr_it";s:242:"Alavert si usa per il trattamento sintomatico delle allergie come lo starnutire, la lacrimazione oculare e l'aumento delle secrezioni nasali. Si usa anche per la cura dell'orticaria e il prurito di persone affette da reazione cutanea cronica.";s:10:"full_descr";s:3827:"<p><strong>INDICATIONS</strong></p><p>Loratadine is an antihistamine that reduces the effects of natural chemical histamine in the body. Histamine can produce symptoms of sneezing, itching, watery eyes, and runny nose. Alavert is used for relieving symptoms of seasonal allergies.</p><p><strong>INSTRUCTIONS</strong></p><p>Use exactly as directed on the label, or as prescribed by your doctor. Do not use in larger or smaller amounts or for longer than recommended.</p><p>Do not crush, chew, or break the regular loratadine tablet. Swallow the pill whole.<br />Measure liquid medicine with a special dose-measuring spoon or medicine cup, not with a regular table spoon.</p><p>Alavert is usually taken once per day. Follow your doctor's instructions.</p><p>To take Alavert orally disintegrating tablet:</p><ul><li>Keep the tablet in its blister pack until you are ready to take the medicine. Open the package and peel back the foil from the tablet blister. Do not push a tablet through the foil or you may damage the tablet.</li><li>Do not swallow the tablet whole. Allow it to dissolve in your mouth without chewing.</li><li>Do not swallow the tablet whole. Allow it to dissolve in your mouth without chewing.</li><li>Using dry hands, remove the tablet and place it on your tongue. It will begin to dissolve right away.</li><li>Take Alavert by mouth with food.</li></ul><p><strong>STORAGE</strong></p><p>Store at room temperature between 20 and 25 degrees C and away from moisture, light and heat.&nbsp;Do not store in the bathroom. Keep in a tight, light-resistant container. Keep Alavert out of the reach of children and away from pets.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>SAFETY INFORMATION</strong></p><p><strong>You should not take Alavert if:</strong></p>
<p>You are allergic to loratadine or to desloratadine (Clarinex).&nbsp;<br />Ask a doctor or pharmacist if it is safe for you to take this medicine if you have:</p>
<ul>
<li>kidney disease;&nbsp;<br />Ask a doctor or pharmacist if it is safe for you to take this medicine if you have:
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>kidney disease;</li>
<li>liver disease.</li>
</ul>
<p>You should not take this medication if you are allergic to loratadine or to desloratadine (Clarinex).</p>
<p>FDA pregnancy category B: This medication is not expected to be harmful to an unborn baby. Tell your doctor if you are pregnant or plan to become pregnant during treatment. Loratadine can pass into breast milk and may harm a nursing baby. Do not use this medication without telling your doctor if you are breast-feeding a baby. <br /><br />Loratadine disintegrating tablets (Claritin Reditab, Alavert) may contain phenylalanine. Talk to your doctor before using this form of loratadine if you have phenylketonuria (PKU).<br /> Do not give this medication to a child younger than 6 years old without the advice of a doctor.</p>
</li>
</ul><p><strong>SIDE EFFECTS</strong></p><p>All medicines may cause side effects, but many people have no, or minor, side effects.<br /><br />Check with your doctor if any of these most common side effects persist or become bothersome:</p>
<ul>
<li>fast or uneven heart rate;</li>
<li>feeling like you might pass out;</li>
<li>jaundice (yellowing of your skin or eyes);</li>
<li>seizures (convulsions).</li>
</ul>
<p>Call your doctor at once if you noticed these serious side effects. Get emergency medical help if you have any of these signs of an allergic reaction: hives; difficult breathing; swelling of your face, lips, tongue, or throat.</p>
<p>Less serious side effects may include:</p>
<ul>
<li>headache;</li>
<li>skin rash;</li>
<li>nervousness;</li>
<li>nosebleed;</li>
<li>feeling tired or drowsy;</li>
<li>eye redness, blurred vision;</li>
<li>stomach pain, diarrhea;</li>
<li>dry mouth, sore throat hoarseness.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>";s:13:"full_descr_de";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_fr";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_es";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_it";s:0:"";s:9:"min_price";s:9:"0.4412864";s:9:"pack_name";s:5:"pills";s:4:"type";s:2:"mg";s:7:"analogs";a:2:{s:8:"Claritin";s:9:"Allergies";s:8:"Clarinex";s:9:"Allergies";}s:8:"synonims";a:277:{i:0;s:7:"Winatin";i:1;s:8:"Vixidone";i:2;s:8:"Vincidal";i:3;s:6:"Versal";i:4;s:7:"Velodan";i:5;s:6:"Valket";i:6;s:6:"Vagran";i:7;s:4:"Utel";i:8;s:6:"Tuulix";i:9;s:8:"Trimidex";i:10;s:6:"Tricel";i:11;s:6:"Tirlor";i:12;s:6:"Tinnic";i:13;s:7:"Talorat";i:14;s:7:"Tidilor";i:15;s:9:"Symphoral";i:16;s:11:"Solusedante";i:17;s:7:"Sohotin";i:18;s:7:"Sitinir";i:19;s:7:"Sinaler";i:20;s:6:"Silora";i:21;s:8:"Sensibit";i:22;s:7:"Sanelor";i:23;s:17:"Sandoz loratadine";i:24;s:6:"Salora";i:25;s:7:"Safetin";i:26;s:6:"Rupton";i:27;s:7:"Rotadin";i:28;s:7:"Roletra";i:29;s:6:"Rohist";i:30;s:5:"Ritin";i:31;s:10:"Ristotadin";i:32;s:7:"Rinolan";i:33;s:6:"Rihest";i:34;s:7:"Rinityn";i:35;s:7:"Ridamin";i:36;s:9:"Rhinos sr";i:37;s:9:"Rhinigine";i:38;s:9:"Restamine";i:39;s:7:"Ralinet";i:40;s:7:"Ramitin";i:41;s:5:"Relor";i:42;s:8:"Rahistin";i:43;s:14:"Pulmosan aller";i:44;s:9:"Profadine";i:45;s:6:"Pretin";i:46;s:8:"Pressing";i:47;s:10:"Pollentyme";i:48;s:22:"Polaramine reformulado";i:49;s:18:"Otrivin loratadine";i:50;s:6:"Orinil";i:51;s:4:"Orin";i:52;s:7:"Oramine";i:53;s:6:"Oradin";i:54;s:6:"Onemin";i:55;s:7:"Nularef";i:56;s:10:"Novacloxab";i:57;s:8:"Nufalora";i:58;s:7:"Nosedin";i:59;s:6:"Niltro";i:60;s:6:"Neoday";i:61;s:15:"Narine repetabs";i:62;s:9:"Nalergine";i:63;s:7:"Mosedin";i:64;s:6:"Mildin";i:65;s:16:"Merck-loratadine";i:66;s:18:"Maxiclear hayfever";i:67;s:5:"Lotal";i:68;s:6:"Lostop";i:69;s:7:"Loropoz";i:70;s:6:"Lormeg";i:71;s:8:"Loritine";i:72;s:7:"Loritin";i:73;s:7:"Loritex";i:74;s:6:"Lorita";i:75;s:8:"Loristal";i:76;s:7:"Lorinol";i:77;s:6:"Lorine";i:78;s:8:"Lorinase";i:79;s:5:"Lorin";i:80;s:7:"Lorimox";i:81;s:7:"Lorihis";i:82;s:7:"Loridin";i:83;s:11:"Loriden gmp";i:84;s:5:"Lorid";i:85;s:7: